Date:  0/0/1882
Source:  Brighter Britain
Author:  HAY
Vol / Page:  2/229
Edition:
Quote:  The Hotete is the so-called `vegetating caterpillar'. it is a grub two or three inches long, and out of its head there grows a parasitic fungus (Spaeria Robertsii) ... The natives eat the hotete. it is

the larva of  Hepialus virescens, a kind of locust.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1904
Source:  Maori Race, The
Author:  TREGEAR
Vol / Page:  86
Edition:
Quote:   ... careful watch was also kept upon the growing plants to guard them from the ravages of a certain caterpillar; the larva of a large  moth (anuhe, awhato, hotete; Cordiceps  robertsii) which preyed on the kumara leaves ... This pest is better known as the `vegetable caterpillar' from a fungus that grows from it after death.
